727820f-b.text:
Queens Boulevard, south side, west from 75th Road, showing the thoroughfare after it was modernised. The building with the sloping roof, that looks like a church, is a fire house of the Nsw York City Fire Department, at 75th Avenue. Shown, too, are newly-built small houses
and apartment houses.
View 2 shows the same area, looking east from 73rd
Road.
P. L. Sperr  View 1: February 10, 1937
